          <avActivityHighlights>High avalanche danger will prevail.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>A lot of new snow. As a consequence of new snow and wind the prevalence and size of the avalanche prone locations will increase. The snowpack will be in most cases unstable. Natural avalanches are possible over a wide area. Avalanches can penetrate deep layers reach very large size. As a consequence of the precipitation moist avalanches are possible. &lt;br/&gt; Without question, it is inadvisable to engage in backcountry touring.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>Somewhat older wind slabs remain for the foreseeable future prone to triggering. As a consequence of new snow and wind, further wind slabs will form. &lt;br/&gt; Numerous weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on shady slopes.</snowpackStructureComment>
